premise_source_doc_sentence: Al-Qaeda also opposes what it regards as man-made laws , and wants to replace them with a strict form of sharia law .

Sa'ad Al-Faqih asserts that authorities , such as the United States government , wish to vilify him because they are allies with the current Saudi regime , which he opposes and denies all allegations.BBC five '' reported a claim that in 1996 Saad Al Faqih purchased an Exact-M 22 satellite phone for Osama bin Laden , an allegation which has not even been investigated , nor has he been charged by any court in the world .
` Al-Faqih 's organisation opposes the current sociopolitical and religious policy of Saudi Arabia .

In mid-2013 , al-Fadhli was sent to Syria on behalf of al-Qaeda emir , Ayman al-Zawahiri , in order to mediate disputes between al-Qaeda 's then Iraqi branch , the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant  (  ISIL  )  and the al-Nusra Front .
According to the U.S. Department of Treasury , al-Fadhli fought with the Taliban and al-Qaeda in Afghanistan as the second-in-command to an unnamed al-Qaeda leader .
